Adding '--detail' param is good idea but I should use this param in the REST API call too.

IMO, 2 views is enough: detailed and non-detaild"}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-11-16 16:28:32.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Hi Ivan,

Thank you for your comment.

Currently Cinder already has two types of volume list in the API, summary and detail. The summary view only returns volume ID and Name, but this implementation is same as Nova's one.

Also detail view return much information related to volume, and this also same implementation of Nova's one. I think changing API affects backward compatibility, so it is better to use API as is.

Nova list CLI command calls detail list API and then always masks unnecessary information to avoid user's confusion. So I'd like to try same implementation to take into cinder client.

IMO these are important fields and others should be masked as default view.(only show --detail is specified)

[ID, Status, Name, Size, Volume Type, Bootable, Attached to]

Also --minimal and --fields are supported at Nova, I think --fields is worth to add cinder client when user want to customize their necessary columns.

Any thought?"}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2015-11-16 16:40:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Mitsuhiro, 

As mentioned above, we've already have 'summary' and 'detailed' view in the API. I'm OK if we'll have a similar feature in the client.

Introducing more options in the client to show more or less columns makes client more complicated both from the developers and users point of view.

If we already pass something from API to client, why we can't just show it to users? 

Also, I like an option to show only needed fields."}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-11-16 17:02:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

I understand that adding more options such as --detail or --minimal to increase confusion for users/admins.

I'd like to suggest that we change the default CLI list view only showing these eight fields same behaviour of Juno.

[ID, Status, Name, Size, Volume Type, Bootable, Attached to]
(Just remove Migration Status and Multiattach from default CLI list view.)

And then add --fields option to show the list with more flexibility."}, {'account_id': 10115, 'date': '2015-11-17 22:25:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-17 23:43:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified+1

commit_message:
Add optional argument to list subcommand

Cinder list command was intended to show summary of
volumes, but currently the command shows many entries
than we expected.

This patch adds these two fixes to show volume list
more simply.

- Remove 'migration status' and 'multiattach' from
  default list view.

- Add '--field' optional argument to 'list' subcommand.
  This argument allows users to show only specified
  entries. Unavailable fields will be ignored from
  the list result.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Iad4bf76e87f84b6e57ec59d134b9413fcad16ce8
Closes-Bug: #1502639

commit_message:
Move Detail page styling into theme

This patch creates a breadcrumb header component and moves the detail
styling into the theme. This should make it easier for themes to
override.

- Alter the breadcrumb header padding, so that everything is aligned correctly
  after the bootstrap tabs patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/246004/
- Add a small margin under tabs, to account for both details and
  workflows; remove the previous workflows-only padding.

Change-Id: I11034d30de900eda50bbc92c275194b6ec731c0d
Closes-Bug: 1516021

commit_message:
Removes unused argument from set_qos_specs

Removes vm_name argument, which was not used. The method
was introduced in the current version and it can be safely
removed.

Change-Id: I016334a400144d4bc1993e020563225d38f9f1d9

commit_message:
Fix the bug of "Error spelling of 'explicitely'"

The word "explicitely" should be spelled as "explicitly".
So it is changed.

(df) Ran spell-check on entire file and fixed a few more
misspellings.

Change-Id: I25d2accc2e0a1aaff71011944a62dadceb508b47
Closes-Bug: #1501202

commit_message:
Add port option support for ipmitool

This adds support for ipmitools port (-p) option allowing operators
to run ipmi on non-default ports.

Change-Id: I9203c2db01cc46a183901c454e98426b4583ce08

Make disk_format configurable

This patch makes disk_format configurable in
rally/verification/tempest/config.py

Added task image exception

Added wait_for_image_task v2

testcase description:

commit_message:
Add support for glance task import

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Glance-tasks-import
Added API for task create, delete and list
Added task image exception
Added wait_for_image for v2
Added wait_for_image_task v2
Added a testcase.
testcase description:
- creating a task for imported dummy image via http
- converting the disk_format for the image
- wait till new created image will be in ready status
- verify image disk_format and task status and type
I am planning to commit more tests for different disk formats.

Change-Id: If4fedc318359603767bc9ec49af572feade7f4bc

commit_message:
Adds nosec to system call in NetcatSocket._terminate

This patch adds "# nosec" comment to os.system call in the
NetcatSocket._terminate function to avoid having it be reported
during the gate test as the call is identified as safe.

Change-Id: I56685e9fca50a7d30656379ccf06dc5769fff9e7
Closes-bug: #1523535

commit_message:
Consider 'in-use' a non-pending volume for caching

We don't cache volume list if one of the volumes is in pending state, as
otherwise we'd miss the cloud-side cache invalidation. However, active
volumes that are attached are in state "in-use" - so basically if you
had one active volume, the cache would never cache.

Change-Id: I03cbc1b814e4a5829936a22751ee81d52b83fb2e

commit_message:
Allow 'is_public' to be set on protected resources

Since *is_public* is meta-information on all objects rather
than content, sahara should allow it to be changed even if *is_protected*
is True. This will make it simpler for users to share protected
objects.

Change-Id: I016bec5282787dba37071af70b16a89764658137
Partial-implements: blueprint allow-public-on-protected

commit_message:
Remove an extra dangling doc reference to CDN

This user guide snuck past the effort in
I529c4901e11161158ce5c35df3bff2ecbbb3091a to remove the CDN service. It
was showing up in a warning message during doc builds.

Change-Id: I2670d98078fcdeab5b0cf36a7ff2c0e4b50cbc3b

commit_message:
[V3] Rename get_credential to show_credential

[GET /resources] methods should be "list_<resource name>s"
or "show_<resource name>", so this patch applies the rule
to credentials client.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I07c4403e42d6f2c7617f455a8a4f292ff10e7059

commit_message:
Use interfaces_client from tempest-lib

The files below have been migrated to tempest-lib

 * interfaces_client.py: I758cf64ba1e6f760a60ed253cb9a8c9bc75ba73b
 * interfaces.py: I758cf64ba1e6f760a60ed253cb9a8c9bc75ba73b
 * test_interfaces_client.py: I758cf64ba1e6f760a60ed253cb9a8c9bc75ba73b

Now Tempest-lib provides those as stable interfaces. So Tempest should
start using those from lib and remove its own copy.

Change-Id: I0d488b89f4f75df55fb7490771d7cb8766ec275e

When refactoring wait_for(), the status variable was accidentally
quoted, which prevented reverting a resize from working. This fixes
that and adds tests to ensure that it stays fixed.

Change-Id: Iba15c6cc07f190a073ed0e785973987b10e499c8
'}]
commit_message:
Remove excessive quotes in _revert_resize()

When refactoring wait_for(), the status variable was accidentally
quoted, which prevented reverting a resize from working. This fixes
that and adds tests to ensure that it stays fixed.

Change-Id: Iba15c6cc07f190a073ed0e785973987b10e499c8

commit_message:
Fix live migration, updating the method checking job results

The method checking job results has been moved to jobutils, while
in livemigrationutils, it's still called from vmutils.

This patch fixes the issue by using the right method.

Change-Id: I8262cd7b44166d106600056637af819e93513ed2

Update extensions links

Extensions links are out-of-date. They are either
invalid or pointing to an old repository [1].

This patch fixes such links.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/identity-api

commit_message:
Temporarily set astara_boot_command in config

Our published image is currently 1 commit behind trunk, so we need
to point this at the old console script until a newer image shows up
with the rename in place.

This can be reverted after mitaka-1.

Change-Id: Ieae165c98f23a1ff20ec75a09d79e495537cea2b

commit_message:
Python 3: Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.loads instead of json.loads

The former always returns the proper type.

This patch fixes:

cinder.tests.unit.api.contrib.test_volume_host_attribute
cinder.tests.unit.api.contrib.test_volume_migration_status_attribute
cinder.tests.unit.api.contrib.test_volume_tenant_attribute

Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-python3

commit_message:
Make the db migration scripts complete

The current db migration scripts cannot reflect the db model we used.
This patch adds migration scripts for service related db and
some alterations on device and device attribute tables.

Change-Id: I3a44c05280c4fa0b6bdb9737ec32200d641f2ac0
Closes-bug: 1518072

commit_message:
Only deploy .my.cnf file on galera/utility containers

The original bug was opened because .my.cnf (with sensitive root credentials)
was being deployed on compute hosts without needing to be there. This patch
restricts the deployment of .my.cnf files to the galera/utility containers
only. This improves security while still allowing deployers to diagnose galera
server issues on the galera server containers themselves, and to access the
database from the utility containers for diagnostic purposes.

Closes-bug: 1510596
Implements: blueprint limit-mysql-config-distribution
Change-Id: I42f39cbfcb02b97846894592d642ac0c58a82b02
(cherry picked from commit e0d58a99debd017ec063b71f290c373892f8b0a3)

commit_message:
Remove grenade-neutron-sideways job

This job was never used for its intended purpose and now there doesn't
seem to be much interest in having an automated, tested upgrade from
nova net to neutron. Since this isn't useful just remove it.

Change-Id: I55715461cb1691336352a364a5dad07c83b50fd0

commit_message:
Update requirements to suit the existence of lxc vg

If lxc volume group exists, the aio will try to use
this volume group to create the containers.

As one container will use a hard 5GB of storage, and
the fact that (by default) there is more than 16
containers, you'll exhaust all your storage space
and the aio build will fail.

This commit should make this failure more clear to
openstack-ansible users.

The amount of disk is counted with the default
install.

Change-Id: I84f68a24423f9e7046b1235ef51bf2291708fcec
(cherry picked from commit dfc544fed974c81d7542ff8167d6a4143914c79c)

commit_message:
Improve log messages from scheduler

Ensure that an unbound method is never logged as "<method name> from None".

Also report the actual action name when doing stack_action().

Change-Id: Iff37860525d182e6eee01a7cc52c6599f05bff8c
Related-Bug: #1339759

commit_message:
Bump rackspace-monitoring-cli version

The current version (v0.6.8) has some issues that mean if the raxmon-cli
fails out it doesn't return the appropriate error code.

This patch bumps the version to v0.6.10 which has a fix included for
this bug.

Change-Id: Icb20df78e1e80282b557cbd3d239199771cdb820
Closes-Bug: #1523610

commit_message:
Revert "Update decorator "update_ostf""

This reverts commit d24ff288ee8092c451ccf138acfc2cf9b0beecd2.
Looks like import CephHA test class directly leads to 
double case execution(ceph_radosgw), so lets revert the patch to unblock CI 
Change-Id: Ifd6ca4afa77f3a5462401e5ff4155bbba408aa0a

Add ability to deploy Murano CloudFoundry Service Broker API

Since Murano has new service CloudFoundry Service Broker API we need
to have an ability to deploy it in MOS 8.0

Implements: bp implement-support-for-murano-service-broker
Change-Id: I338477269a73cb342115511b99bd004c37a43512

commit_message:
Python3 readiness for congress (misc changes)

Changes:
- Explicit conversion of dict view objects to lists for comparison with list
- Explicit copy of dict for iteration while changing dict

Result:
- all congress/tests/* tests pass under tox -epy34.
- py34 gating vote may be enabled along with this patch, to prevent regression
- bugs likely remain which are not caught by unit tests

Partially implements blueprint: support-python3

Change-Id: I4927f4875e8f86464b3c9fc7c63f918945cc359e

commit_message:
Convert instance_flavor configs from IntOpt to StrOpt

Nova instances are not limited to integer IDs and this is required
to support instance flavors with UUIDs or str IDs.

Closes-bug: #1515000
Change-Id: I1abf665f43cb33c1d1d2bd612aed750cae3455a6

commit_message:
Refactor: Remove use of self where not needed

In test_v3_resource, some tests create local
entities scoped to the test class instance, as
opposed to scoped only to the test method.

This patch fixes such occurrences.

Change-Id: Ie4f1e2e61d89fa10a99c9bebd2b9bd06fccd7c6a

commit_message:
Revert "Move netifaces to extras"

For now revert this, at a later date we can reapply
this but we need to order this a little differently to
make it work out.

commit_message:
Refactor: Move uncommon entities from setUp

In test_v3_resource, a group and a credential
entities are created but only used by 2 methods.

This patch moves those entities from the setUp
method to the specific tests which need them.

Change-Id: Ib73cea79f2b0f4315022049a78c6b77550ea697a

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary extra instance saves during resize

In different resize operations (prep/finish/confirm/revert), flavor
settings are updated to keep track of current/old/new flavor for an
instance. Helper methods in the Instance object that used to assist
with on-the-fly conversion of flavor info from its old storage location
in system metadata to instance extra are used. This conversion is no
longer necessary and calling these helpers cause a large number of
extra saves to happen for no good reason.

This change makes sure no extra saves are done by reworking the code
to eliminate the use of helpers set_flavor() and delete_flavor().

Change-Id: Iaf5379089796f82289602c471608db38b3052904

commit_message:
Catch FixedIpNotFoundForAddress when create server

FixedIpNotFoundForAddress is not catched during server creation,
so 500 error is reported to client side.

Change-Id: I3cd45cd63c962225d6a893ad0fdeb01ecb94e784

commit_message:
Don't emit confusing error in netns-cleanup

If we're trying to delete a dhcp/qrouter device with use_veth
= False (Which is the default for some time), we'll first
try to 'ip link del %s', which will fail and emit a confusing
error, then try 'ovs-vsctl del-port'. There's no need to
log an error in such a case.

The patch attempts to future proof by setting the
set_log_fail_as_error(False) to be as tight as possible, so we
do log errors in case the device is somehow used in the future.

Change-Id: I1954bde3ee9a2e43d7615717134b61c5fa7cfbb1
Closes-Bug: #1463800

commit_message:
neutron: only get port id when listing ports in validate_networks

The validate_networks method is called from the compute API before
casting off to build instances. If the project has a lot of ports, the
list call to neutron can be slow, so we should optimize this method as
much as possible. One way to do that is rather than get the port details
back, we just get the id since all we care about is the number of ports
assigned to the project.

Closes-Bug: #1521788

Change-Id: Icddba161112526dde23184ee80ad5cb60fe66cc6

commit_message:
neutron: only list ports if there is a quota limit when validating

The list_ports call can take awhile if the project has a lot of ports.
If it turns out that there is unlimited quota, then we don't even need
to list the ports, so move that after the show_quota call.

Partial-Bug: #1521788

Change-Id: I4d128f182283ffa4479934f640a67d9c536824b5

commit_message:
Config options: centralize section "scheduler"

This change moves all of the configuration options previously defined in
nova/scheduler to the new centralized nova/conf/scheduler directory.

A subsequent patch will then improve the help texts.

Blueprint centralize-config-options
Change-Id: I08d50e873f71601a26ce768feac635243d0570f4

commit_message:
Don't track migrations in 'accepted' state

This state was added during Liberty for evacuate, and since it's the
first state that is assigned to the migration record on it's creation,
and before we start using it for resource tracking, there is no reason
to consider those records as "in progress".

Change-Id: I2a9bbe87bc1518cee9e43e4eeec1fa585305f423
Related-bug: 1417667

commit_message:
live-migrate: Change the status Migration is created with

We want to be consistent with what resize does here, and there should be
no difference with regards to resource tracking (i.e. resources now
should not be tracked for this state).

Partial-bug: 1417667
Change-Id: I75f914fb28e337df48e8e68ae7e407b5239d2647

commit_message:
compute: split check_can_live_migrate_destination

We'll want to add claims around the logic of this method, so it's better
if there is a nested method that does the business logic to
avoid deep nesting that makes the code less readable.

Related-bug: 1417667
Change-Id: I8c2f1a67846fe27dbe350a288d7e9be6be109b90

commit_message:
Initiate docker pulls before docker-compose

This tries to pull all the overcloud images before docker-compose run
is attempted, which means the containers can be started faster. On my
system I saw a speed up of around two minutes for overcloud
deployment.

Change-Id: I18f56933e75e7aba97f27dcf91075de0d3e8ff05

commit_message:
Adjust build script to not use rev-parse

The gate's post-jobs run from a detached head. Using rev-parse yields
the last commit of master as opposed to the newly merged commit.
Use and parse git-log instead.

Change-Id: I2c4d8501191a95005e566f2c594a3d880b688096

commit_message:
Generate data_table.html

This patch updates reviewday so that it generates
both an index.html and a separate data_table.html
which can be used for importing the reviewday HTML
table into an externally styled website.

The existing reviewday OpenStack style remains the same.
This patch should prove useful for sites wishing
to re-use the "data table" format as-is inside of a
separately themed web site.

Change-Id: If9a69235484038e4b10ee8a2c66ed834f5f6a8d2

commit_message:
Ability to set the launchpad project name

Some projects use share a common Launchpad project for
reporting bugs (they don't always have split out
projects for these things). This patch updates
reviewday the --project-file format to support
specifying an altername 'launchpad_project' default.

Change-Id: I66afed988afe4c0cfa37d269fd397bcbb9e5badf

commit_message:
Rename tenant_id to project_id

Since openstack is going through renaming tenants to projects
it is best that we do this now while its easier before it becomes
bigger and harder to do.

This also adds project_id to the health_monitor table and models
since this seemed like an oversight.

Change-Id: Icc8034dcb517a3f8d218d83c94e4a2dcc977cc29

commit_message:
Move resource related testcase into their own module

Since domains and projects has been split into their own backend,
these testcases which are specified to test against domain or
project should be move into a new test module.

Partially implements: bp pluggable-assignments
Change-Id: Ia4ee5d5d5522e8cc084423cd2a458db04b33c341

commit_message:
Update decorator "update_ostf"

- make updating of ostf-server code via package
not via the patch
- add test gate_ostf_update

Next variables should be exported:
UPDATE_FUEL=True
UPDATE_FUEL_PATH=/path/to/dir/with/package

Change-Id: I2c2b270292a9d5f529607d91b3282669c320cbe7
Closes-Bug: #1517487

commit_message:
Fix db error when running python34 Unit tests

If tests for py27 is executed before py34 tests, then
there is a chance that py34 related tests may fail.
The following patch fixes it by reordering the tests
from py27 -> py34 to py34 -> py27.

Ref: https://review.openstack.org/#/q/status:merged++topic:bug/1489059,n,z

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I721bd37ce9a796dcd92d44876e803294d06af5b6
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Fix exceptions.from_response() parameter

The exceptions.from_response() from the common.apiclient.exceptions
module takes 'method' as it's second param.

Co-Authored-By: Lucas Alvares Gomes <lucasagomes@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: #1520528
Change-Id: I7d59c2f6dcdf181f561f38f95b460e556e8b6d9e

entire project.

commit_message:
WIP: iso element compatability for ubuntu EFI

The pre-existing EFI boot support for the ISO element
only worked for Fedora or if somehow the files were
present.

This breaks the dependency to the grub2 element in an
attempt to do the right thing per operating system as
each OS's packages and install processes may conflict
when all that is needed is the essential files for
booting images.

Image creation tested with "ubuntu-signed ironic-agent iso"

Change-Id: I03d9c5bba4f9be793814bb6207ebc135f0fca464

commit_message:
Add list of supported stores to help

The glance-api.conf help is autogenerated from the glance_store
help.

To display the full list of stores available for the 'stores'
parameter in the glance_store section of glance-api.conf add
them to the relevant glance_store help comment.

Change-Id: Ie69e1db0959e22e07a47943874b6710a063fbc1d
Partial-bug: 1521236
(cherry picked from commit 815e463a42bce80a79e8471052c03bbf488de2c4)

commit_message:
Update run_tests to be more complete

This patch updates the run_tests convenience script to make it
execute all test environments using tox, but also ensures that
all the correct pre-requisites are in place before doing so.

Change-Id: I24ede2d40a33bc50ae93277d53dfd31af3294674

commit_message:
Rname oslo config generator config file

The dev env docs provide the following command:

oslo-config-generator --config-file
     etc/oslo-config-generator/searchlight.conf

This was updated with the following patch,
but the oslo config generator config file wasn't actually renamed.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/245622/

With this commit, the config file searchlight-api.conf have
been renamed to etc/oslo-config-generator/searchlight.conf

Closes-Bug: #1523648

Change-Id: I44a810885d4b8174dfc7f4f8d7e2c59fcef41d80
Co-Authored-By: Gábor Antal <antal@inf.u-szeged.hu>

commit_message:
Trival: Remove 'MANIFEST.in'

Everything in this file is automatically generated by pbr. There
appears to be no good reason to keep it around.
More details please see:
https://github.com/openstack-dev/pbr/blob/master/pbr/packaging.py#L384

Change-Id: I48e3a0129949747759acb68984f1e0425185e032

commit_message:
Add new parameter `choices` to Integer type

There is a need to add choices to PortOpt. So make Integer type accept
choices parameter first.
Choices options will provide a set of valid values. min/max provide a range
of values. They are mutally exclusive.

Change-Id: I0906b6e2309d751d7c31589fc3da8e5f3026bf64

commit_message:
Add the version attribute to the Client class

There is a way to get the version of the API being used. We need such
feature to work correct with different versions of the Cinder API
from third-party tools.

Change-Id: Ifde689df08644f9452138a9cd22052bc57fcb5d5

commit_message:
Add a callable to gather extra data for fps

ObjectVersionChecker gathers a group of relevant data with which it then
generates a fingerprint. This change adds a callable to get_hashes() to
provide the object class, which the callable can then use to gather more
data upon which it wants the fingerprint to be generated. This allows
end users to version on more than just fields and methods.

Change-Id: Ibbaaf926d50693ed0ddd96132542830dba75a285

commit_message:
Remove incomplete CDN code

OpenStack Poppy, the CDN service, was going to be added in here, but it
never ended up being completed. This change removes an empty proxy class
and a few template documentation mentions. This should be added
eventually, but should not exist right now since we're not going to be
fleshing out the details between now and 1.0 anyway.

Change-Id: I529c4901e11161158ce5c35df3bff2ecbbb3091a

Remove python 2.6 classifier since py26 is not supported

Python 2.6 support was dropped pre-Liberty, but we did not update the
project classifier.

commit_message:
remove MANIFEST.in since it is not needed

The exisiting manifest file actually didn't not change the contents of
the package.  It referred to files that were no longer present or
automatically included via normal file discovery when packaging.

Change-Id: Idfd65b433c9f4022baff3dd790c0599c94f77602

commit_message:
Remove unused, broken keystone::dev::install class

This hasn't been changed since 2012 and has comments all over it that
indicate that it didn't work all that well then.  It references classes
in the puppet-openstack module that is no longer supported.  It predates
the current location for requirements.txt in the upstream keystone
repository.

Change-Id: I5b992e60264fe2f45b9ea4ed3799bbf55f4dc38d

commit_message:
Add tox env for running a local dev instance of the dashboard

This commit adds a new tox env to locally run the whole dashboard
with an api server talking to the infra subunit2sql db. This is
useful for locally testing the whole workflow.

Change-Id: I7827d5d23606d645a51d5658e9ad6685a1bc84a7

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on py34
we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch
puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem
to happen.

Change-Id: I32d54c979ca061f916d771ce799120d812121ff5
Closes-Bug: #1489059

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-12-03 00:58:13.000000000', 'message': 'Add hooks for external install & svc management

This adds defined anchor points for external modules to hook into the
software install, config and service dependency chain.  This allows
external modules to manage software installation (virtualenv,

commit_message:
Add hooks for external install & svc management

This adds defined anchor points for external modules to hook into the
software install, config and service dependency chain.  This allows
external modules to manage software installation (virtualenv,
containers, etc) and service management (pacemaker) without needing rely
on resources that may change or be renamed.

Change-Id: I0b524e354b095f2642fd38a2f88536d15bcdf855

should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

commit_message:
Avoid duplicate client resource

python-openstackclient is used by a few other classes, so switch to
ensure_resource to avoid duplicate package declarations.

Partial-Bug: #1523643

Change-Id: I437b266344cf6ace683379c1999fc08fbdee756c
(cherry picked from commit 8469027d44ee05b8b204ce382266eae92f41ae29)

commit_message:
Implement Gnocchi dispatcher

* Add dispatcher options to ceilometer::collector.
* Create ceilometer::dispatcher::gnocchi class, with current upstream options.
* Add an example of manifest.
* Unit & functional tests.

Note:
This patch implement os_service_defaults only for the new class.
For collector, it will be updated in one patch in another patchset.

Change-Id: Id9364e1e1337708b1e0254b4c6268f1a0b1a42ad
(cherry picked from commit f47c52f26dadc767728ebc8cba5cdfe251d94c2d)

no plural.

commit_message:
Disable auto activation of all volumes

A problem was discovered that occurs during the provisioning of an
Atomic host with ironic causing a kernel panic. The problem is that
during provisioning the thin-pool associated with the provisioned VM was
being auto-activated on the instack host.

With containerized deployments becoming more popular, this is an
important fix to get in now. The workaround of defining the
auto_activation_volume_list to an empty list should be unobtrusive to
any operations on the undercloud.

Closes-bug: #1521733

Change-Id: I0ebb6488b0c061b0aed00ad1560126126ef3777c

commit_message:
Exit early if EMAIL envvar is not defined

announce.sh supposes the EMAIL environment variable is set
(since it calls release-notes without setting it.

Exit early with an error message if it's not set.

Change-Id: Ic9f00478dfeca69c4ecbe5fc126105c445c34c4e

commit_message:
Fix silent error in case of missing meta

If run against a tag missing the meta lines, announce.sh silently
fails. This makes it slightly more verbose.

Change-Id: Id60b5c1b50c0eff1dc802219b2fb4f7ed444d165

commit_message:
make manual releases easier with option to generate announcement

Add -a option to release_from_yaml.sh and release.sh, causing the latter
to trigger announce.sh to generate the release announcement. This saves
a couple of extra manual steps, since the announce script can run
against the already cloned project repository with the new tag, instead
of having to do that step separately. The option is only meant to be
used when the scripts are run interactively.

Change-Id: I3449ca119d42c0317de2aa0fc5441091acfe49e1

  remove them from the spec.
- Add information about 'reexecute_on' task parameter.

commit_message:
Remove juno handling from Jenkins

With Juno EOL, we do not need to check for stable/juno anymore.
Remove handling of stable/juno from jenkins jobs.
Also remove special -juno
jobs from both jenkins and zuul for trove and devstack-gate.

Change-Id: I41f31ea1f15ffe71b57197040dac3bb447900dad

commit_message:
Remove juno branch handling for python projects

With Juno EOL, we do not need to check for stable/juno anymore.

Remove filter from python-ceilometerclient, python-glanceclient,
python-keystoneclient, python-neutronclient, python-swiftclient.

Change-Id: I47b8b52ef6e8fae6803e7ff448d774d28cdf7190

commit_message:
Validate requested new vhd size when performing resizes

Nova and Cinder need to validate the new vhd size before performing
resizes.

For convenience, this validation will be performed by the VHDUtils
resize method.

Change-Id: I56d2ac9da4d56b62abd427c926a04d9134863036

Fixes failing unit tests related to file opening

Recent changes added unit tests that mock opening files.
Those unit tests are failing under certain dependencies.

Change-Id: Id7d0b259d3343664d0f2469684588d6077a195a3

commit_message:
Nova volume-detach --force requires API

In order for 'nova-mange db volume-force-detach' to be implemented, the
python-cinderclient will need to expose Cinder's force_detach.

Change-Id: I194a5191532f6be9e19d76a28628bfd0a439d4cf
Implements: blueprint nova-force-detach-needs-cinderclient-api

This method uses the 'run_and_check_output' wrapper for executing a
kernel32 lib function. The issue is that the 'kernel32_lib_func' flag
was omitted, for which reason the error handling is done improperly.

Namely, this function will return non-zero values in case of success,

This patch fixes the issue by adding the missing flag.

"}]
commit_message:
Fix method retrieving share capacity info

This method uses the 'run_and_check_output' wrapper for executing a
kernel32 lib function. The issue is that the 'kernel32_lib_func' flag
was omitted, for which reason the error handling is done improperly.

Namely, this function will return non-zero values in case of success,
which at the moment is interpreted as an error.

This patch fixes the issue by adding the missing flag.

Change-Id: I63c7323ac9a5a4bd850971b2de67012b78bdbfa5

commit_message:
Remove py26 from tox.ini and setup.cfg

As of https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/python3 openstack
is targeted to py34 and py27 and also dropping py26
for mitaka. And also added solum docs in setup.cfg

Change-Id: Idb2810569321e29bd5d3e09b737d0b2e69552c1c
Closes-Bug: #1523188

need to patch a method to fake the temporary method,

commit_message:
Migrate "network list" command to new version using SDK.

This patch makes "network list" command use sdk.

Since we have to keep the other commands runnable with
the old network client, we use a temporary method to
create sdk network client. And as a result, the tests
need to patch a method to fake the temporary method,
which will be removed at last.

Change-Id: I0882501cd7bb2c17917e10a6da4298f1452c9765
Implements: blueprint neutron-client
Co-Authored-By: Terry Howe <terrylhowe@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Tang Chen <tangchen@cn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
Fix metric for rabbitmq sockets MaaS alarms

This fixes an error where the metric were listed as:
metric["rabbitmq_socket_used"] & metric["rabbitmq_socket_total"]
These should be fixed to be "sockets" rather than "socket".

Closes Bug: #1522897
Change-Id: I63ae2be2a09d2b9fa04c60e48805e42b8f3a5874

commit_message:
Fix _get_tenant_volume_usages

The search opts for volume/snapshot list should be 'all_tenants' and
'project_id' instead of 'alltenants' and 'tenant_id'.

Change-Id: I9ab71421447b3f8fb402247df3290fa3066bf8c5
Closes-bug: #1469589
(cherry picked from commit faa44bfe1d6c4f342b8572bc4939771cda2039c7)

consistency.

commit_message:
Neutron FWaaS: Use generated configuration files if available

Generate the Neutron FWaaS sample config files by using the oslo
generator. The files are generated with a .sample extension and
replace the static example configuration files.

Once the generation code is delivered, the static config files
will be removed.

Change-Id: Ic8208850a27408c8fbeed80ecdb43345aa7dfaa4
Related-blueprint: autogen-neutron-conf-file
Partial-bug: #1199963
Depends-On: I8e9113dfb88e5290f6eedd012d1a52fc35c3c88c

commit_message:
Avoid RequestContextSerializer from oslo.messaging

Oslo.messaging is in the process of removing the class
starting with the change id:
I21d76abf1c30b9e89cb8a6c20d1c0cc79cd83a3f

So ironic should just use its own class. Note that the
next oslo.messaging release will break ironic based on
some local testing.

Change-Id: I618fdc3024b3bc16515216bda900804f4cebba7d

commit_message:
Update tosca-parser requirements

Due to changes in tosca-parser message formats in version 0.3.0
update heat-translator requirements so that version of tosca-parser
is used with latest heat-translator.

Change-Id: I1571cc4316c9febc57cce9fe198eb89c5d747021

commit_message:
Add dev docs for SCSS/and styling in Horizon

This patch adds a topic guide explaining how developers should write and
organise SCSS within Horizon.

Change-Id: I4de2d1da73f6c7977a16fba9d09678923d7c443c
Closes-Bug: 1514869

commit_message:
Fix default value with postgreSQL

When use 'sort-key=size' for multi-pages searching with postgreSQL
DB, it will raise an error: DBError: (psycopg2.DataError). And return
HTTPInternalServerError (HTTP 500) to users. The reason is that
postgreSQL doesn't support the size's default value to be string.
This patch set the size's default value to zero.

Change-Id: Ib3b5f3f57be3683ba274f0122e6314978a79e75f
Closes-bug:#1481154

commit_message:
Deprecate _ builtin translation function

This function is discouraged for usage as per oslo.i18n guidelines [1],
so we should deprecate and remove it.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/usage.html

Change-Id: I848ee1dbd16a23c4db42df4690bf139bd769f3e8
Partial-Bug: #1520094

commit_message:
Remove juno branch handling for manila-swift

With Juno EOL, we do not need to check for stable/juno anymore.

Remove handling for manila, neutron, neutron-fwaas, neutron-lbaas,
neutron-vpnaas, oslo.*, requirements, swift.

Change-Id: Ia907908f08bca565d9ee1cbbe7f4e61667628643

commit_message:
Run neutron dibtest job in experimental queue

In order to better determine if the newer ubuntu-trusty images function
as expected run the neutron dibtest job on them in addition to hte nova
net and multinode jobs.

Change-Id: I08f9eb7abf5dd6cd49e86652d676e9adc6b78e9c

commit_message:
Make some volume related quotas translatable

One static quota (Per volume size (GiB)) and some dynamic quotas
were not being translated due to their dynamic nature.
This patch tries to address that.

Change-Id: I219d36676e21431f434accfdd99dbfb6191519e1
Closes-Bug: #1516684

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-12-04 07:46:35.000000000', 'message': 'Fix header layout after window's width has been resized down to <1285px

Bootstrap CSS sets negative margins to navbar rows, so in case we are
using more than one, successive rows are pushed to avoid overlapping.

Fuel web interface has only one navbar row, so the document layout
becomes broken when it pushes window margin beyond the viewport.

This commit cancels out negative margin-right if the navbar row is the
only child of "nav" element. It works in FF 3.5+, IE9+, Chrome 4+ and
Safari 4+. Bug will be still observable in older browsers without
:only-child CSS3 selector support with no other regressions caused by
this change.

Change-Id: I48a14b2321499e74a46d8f4cd61dc0f71a10fab4
Closes-Bug: 1519375
'}, {'created': '2015-12-04 10:34:49.000000000', 'message': "Fix header layout after window's width has been resized down to <1285px

commit_message:
Fix header layout after window's width has been resized down to <1285px

Bootstrap CSS sets negative margins to navbar rows, so in case we are
using more than one, successive rows are pushed to avoid overlapping.

Fuel web interface has only one navbar row, so the document layout
becomes broken when it pushes window margin beyond the viewport.

This commit cancels out negative margin-right if the navbar row is the
last child of its parent. It works in FF 3.5+, IE9+, Chrome 4+ and
Safari 4+. Bug will be still observable in older browsers without
:last-child CSS3 selector support with no other regressions caused by
this change.

Change-Id: I48a14b2321499e74a46d8f4cd61dc0f71a10fab4
Closes-Bug: 1519375

What about keeping the TEMPLATE_DEBUG as it was on the local_settings.py?

on settings.py, line 270 we import everything from local_settings, so the logic could (should?) be implemented in there instead.

That way, openstack admins dont have to change anything, we keep it simple and it does not look ugly :)'}, {'account_id': 12826, 'date': '2015-12-07 09:53:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

The setting itself is deprecated I believe. If you mix and match you'll get warnings, and it could be removed in the future."}, {'account_id': 12826, 'date': '2015-12-07 09:54:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Also I think TEMPLATE_DEBUG actually uses the same setting as DEBUG, its only in some cases you'd actually want them different."}, {'account_id': 12281, 'date': '2015-12-07 10:00:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

Oh, I see, I thought TEMPLATE_DEBUG was not part of django, my bad!

My point was, have a keyword(e.g. OPENSTACK_TEMPLATE_DEBUG) to enable template debug from local_settings and then on the settings.py do

from local.settings import OPENSTACK_TEMPLATE_DEBUG

TEMPLATES[0]['OPTIONS']['debug'] = OPENSTACK_TEMPLATE_DEBUG

as a way of hiding from the openstack admin the need to set it to that specific [0]['OPTIONS']['debug'], instead providing a simpler, easy to understand, toggle for it."}, {'account_id': 12826, 'date': '2015-12-07 16:56:00.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 12826, 'date': '2015-12-07 16:57:01.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 8040, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:09:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review+1

Results for 500 of fake cinder volumes: 0:22 for cached version vs 1:05 for non-cached.
Results for 1000 of fake cinder volumes: 0:43 for cached version vs 2:05 for non-cached.

Approximate performance gain is ~3 times.

Strongly vote for this change and would recommend for porting to any stable branch (if it was allowed by stable policies). The best performance improvement ever, in terms of LOC / performance gain!'}, {'account_id': 1941, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:09:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review+2

much better, thanks!'}, {'account_id': 8040, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:14:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

Setting up many volumes testing environment in Devstack:

vi /etc/cinder/cinder.conf

Change 'default_volume_type' at [default] to fake-driver, create a separate section then:

[fake-driver]
volume_driver = cinder.volume.drivers.FakeISCSIDriver
volume_backend_name = fake-driver

Then restart both c-vol and c-api services.

After that use something like
i=0;while [ $i -lt <N> ]; do cinder create 1 --display-name MyFirstVolume_$i; (( i++ )); done

where <N> is number of volumes being created."}, {'account_id': 5623, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:30:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-12-07 19:23:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Verified+1

(1 comment)

So I can see the need for this in the context of updating Pool NS records. That's obviously a case where you'll need to NOTIFY every zone in a pool. 

But there are other times where you'd want to throttle NOTIFYs, that aren't really covered by the implementation. Things like:

I'm creating a new recordset on a zone every five seconds, I don't want to send a bajillion notifies for that zone, I want to send one, wait 30 seconds, send another or something.

If I'm at high load, or a periodic process is catching up a lot of things, maybe I want to place a global rate-limit on the number of NOTIFYs that I want mdns to be a able to send."}]

Up until PS8 the PlanManager looked more like a simple, model-like resource to manage the template files in Swift (or whatever store is used).

In PS9 it contains all the methods described in the spec in a single class, some of them more or less just proxying other *Manager instance methods (DeploymentOptionsManager/DeploymentConfigurationManager). I very well miss something here, but I wonder if it would be better to  keep PlanManager a basic CRUD class (and store abstraction) so it can be used by the other *Manager clases that contain the actual business logic to update the environment file.'}, {'account_id': 17888, 'date': '2015-10-02 10:31:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 8532, 'date': '2015-10-02 12:01:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

(1 comment)

"Up until PS8 the PlanManager looked more like a simple, model-like resource to manage the template files in Swift (or whatever store is used).  In PS9 it contains all the methods described in the spec in a single class, some of them more or less just proxying other *Manager instance methods (DeploymentOptionsManager/DeploymentConfigurationManager)."

Correct, in PS9 the plan_store took over the role of the model resource and the PlanManager became the public workflow interface the CLI and REST API will call.

"...I wonder if it would be better to keep PlanManager a basic CRUD class (and store abstraction) so it can be used by the other *Manager clases that contain the actual business logic to update the environment file."

That's one way to look at it.  The idea with the current PS is to keep the classes that do all of the work abstracted underneath the PlanManager class and try to keep the scope of each class to a minimum so we depend on abstraction rather than concrete implementations.'}, {'account_id': 17888, 'date': '2015-10-02 14:55:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

OK, this makes sense. As discussed earlier, I am updating my draft of the DeploymentConfigurationManager accordingly...'}, {'account_id': 7386, 'date': '2015-10-06 16:13:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

commit_message:
Initial workflow implementation of tripleo-common

This patch adds basic implementation for tripleo-common
as defined in the spec[1].  The PlanManager class provides
the workflow for the REST API or CLI interaction.

[1] http://bit.ly/1O5n9JV

Co-Authored-By: Florian Fuchs <flfuchs@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I2be06d7282f9ca44b91d1db22efc0e7ad0096400

commit_message:
Use assertTrue/False instead of assertEqual(T/F)

The usage of assertEqual(True/False, ***) should be changed
to a meaningful format of assertTrue/False(***).
This patch fixes the same in keystone.

Change-Id: I2b67c34796c54b0963fbc7020d4e78ed4f71c7f3
Closes-Bug: #1512207

Showing network configuration saving errors

 - creating a fake check_networks task in case of error
  received from server
- added functional test for data validation error appearence

commit_message:
Adding search options to backup list

Add search options to backup list like volumes and snapshots.

Those tree arguments would be added for do_list method.
Detail query filter would be added at the end of query.
  http://localhost:887/v2/project-id/backups/detail?status=available

blueprint add-filter-options-to-backup-list

Change-Id: I6f1d052bf1f3b53fc12075251e94c5691e61113e

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

[{'created': '2015-07-28 13:59:29.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: Set executor to Putils

The Brick library is dependent on Putils being the executor but
has the option to have a different executor passed in.  If a
different executor is used, it would cause issues in exception
handling.

This is WIP as the testcode needs a lot of clean-up due to
fake-exec being passed in as an executor.  I just wanted some
feedback on if this is the right path before fixing up all
the testcode.

commit_message:
WIP: Set executor to Putils

The Brick library is dependent on Putils being the executor but
has the option to have a different executor passed in.  If a
different executor is used, it would cause issues in exception
handling.

This is WIP as the testcode needs a lot of clean-up due to
fake-exec being passed in as an executor.  I just wanted some
feedback on if this is the right path before fixing up all
the testcode.

Change-Id: I6fc0ee3ac67b1c2bd0db04cb3ec82fdb43a43184
Closes-Bug: #1216051

commit_message:
Clean the unused methods in `volumes.py`

Methods in `volumes.py` are called by `shell.py` in two ways.

- Find the volume instance, call the method in class `Volume`,
  then execute the method defined in class `VolumeManager`.
- Call the method defined in class `VolumeManager` directly.
  For example, cs.volumes.set_metadata(volume, metadata) will
  invoke the method in `VolumeManager` instead of going to
  `Volume` at first.

In the second case, there is no need to define the method in class
`Volume`, this patch clean these unused methods.

Change-Id: Idbd63d0990944c1e3ea739ac842add1916df5989

commit_message:
Add support to return request_id of last request

Thread local storage is used for storing openstack request ids.

Added method 'store_openstack_request_id' which will store request_id
to thread local storage of client. This method is called after request
is made to cinder service.
If authentication fails or succeeds, in both the cases, request_id is
set to None because authenticate method will give a call to the keystone
service, and response header returned will contain request_id
of keystone service.

Added method 'get_openstack_request_id' which will return request_id
stored in thread local storage of client. 'get_openstack_request_id'
method should be called from cross-projects to retrieve the last
request-id from the client for logging purpose, after making api
call to cinder service.

Change-Id: Ie44df57f88584934e4d32da43ae58cc2d485aa74
blueprint: return-req-id

commit_message:
Add support to incremental backups in cinder

Added a new option to "cinder backup-create" to support incremental backups.
Specify --incremental to create an incremental backup. By default, it will
be a full backup.

Co-Authored-By: Xing Yang <xing.yang@emc.com>
Implements: blueprint incremental-backup
Change-Id: Id11ecd2982ea838181b4adaa5a742fc65f864acb
(cherry picked from commit 3ee941c1e6e497f6ac0ad7919c5c0703f5cb3607)

commit_message:
Remove fuel_package_updates module

This functionality is going to be covered by packetary
https://github.com/openstack/fuel-mirror/tree/master/packetary
which implements low level logic for manipulating of
rpm/deb packages and repositories. Packetary can be used
both for creating partial and full mirrors of upstream and MOS
repos.

Change-Id: I8f4ccc71a27a486e6b0042eed6ce2ca8098deb48
DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1517552

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I9b40f6ebdb696a63f39a1d644944d97020f1a714

This patchset was cherry picked to branch stable/liberty as commit 586f8458befe8db10333fdf6f5a7b69abda04597'}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2015-12-08 15:24:47.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I'm not exactly sure why this was needed. The underlying too here (os-net-config) is meant to be idempotent... so it should only re-apply things if a change has been made to the network templates.

What we've done here is something that could hang up someone on an (initial deployment). Say they deploy, and the all-nodes-network validation fails. They make a network templates change... but now (with this commit) it won't get re-applied on the next heat-stack update... unless the user knows to go and set this new internal parameter."}, {'account_id': 12398, 'date': '2015-12-08 16:37:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

I'm not sure what the original goal of this patch was, but I can think of a valid use case for only running os-net-config on CREATE: if an operator needs to make manual network changes to a deployment after deployment, they will not want those changes overwritten by a stack update.

I'm not sure that should be the default mode, but it makes sense to me to have that option."}]

commit_message:
Allows for customization of NetworkDeployment actions

We don't necessarily want the network configuration to be reapplied
with every template update so we add a param to configure on which
action the NetworkDeployment resource should be executed.

Change-Id: I0e86318eb5521e540cc567ce9d77e1060086d48b
Co-Authored-By: Dan Sneddon <dsneddon@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: James Slagle <jslagle@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Jiri Stransky <jstransk@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Steven Hardy <shardy@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Run ceilometer-python34 on all branches

The job was marked to run only on master in
Ifef79456e7caea8ecc5dda6b0ea8b6869eb99f93 - at that time so that it did
not run on juno. Since juno is eol'ed, let's run the job
on all branches now and thus remove the filter.

Change-Id: Ib38ce0a8baf7458f897a44eca4efc280a27a5444

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I6362d9af880ed81bd422a15501a088f83a05953e

Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I1b5adbe9f8636fc007b159fd3e46b4c6e1c38232

commit_message:
Revert "Cap Pillow to fix doc gates"

This reverts commit 930cf4d9c1a3b51d3df07f69273c4273a6f68454.

Adding Pillow to *requirements.txt was a temporary way to set the
upper bound to < 3.0.0

nodepool thick slaves and requirements have been fixed and devstack is
fixed in the patch that this depends on.

Change-Id: I88965256ee0d83d82ba9aad991951c8702aa301f
Depends-On: I2bec8cf1bfeaaa6ae329704229fdeb86d26e55c7

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I3f563f0301bd711332f07e6234bbf330bcbff775

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: Iee9acba9c3659335c23c8794323255c3263c91db

subject: Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: If40eef36cdbd5eab0573feb65759ea387b6cc245

commit_message:
[Sahara] Remove volumes from non-workers

The volumes are used only by the Datanode process
which runs in a worker (or proxy) node group. This is true
for all provisioning plugins.

Change-Id: I826e01e16bb5976558e63a79c6849831c46ea9b7

commit_message:
Add deprecation warning for Qpid rpc driver

Qpid driver is removed from Oslo.messaging [1] in
the Mitaka release. This patch adds warning if this driver
is used.

[1] I4a9cba314c4a2f24307504fa7b5427424268b114

Change-Id: I3edd497babe0ad64c76e7c2e6763ea0fe10be474

commit_message:
Remove empty tabs in freezer dashboard

remove empty tab for job edition
remove possibility to add job without interval if start and end date
are provided
show a message when a job is started/stoped

Resolves bug: 1523497

Change-Id: Iff39fc9e813969672eecd48d9084fd100bcf611c
(cherry picked from commit b48b27fb8c248fa312a0c72fb685c073ec2a8219)

commit_message:
settings: Remove unused setting

SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_DRIVER is no longer honoured by devstack.
This commit just removes it rather than fixing,
because we no longer prefer mysqlconnector over the default pymysql.

Closes-Bug: #1505467
Related-Bug: #1523377
Change-Id: Ic06f90ff56a0e3ab1c15fc53feda4a5ca2dad5c4

commit_message:
Delete python bytecode before every test run.

This should eliminate the need to clean -x -i to kill pyc files in
your local directory to get tests to pass.

Change-Id: I668c1baac23b29750fa19ccb0a4302504399dd75

commit_message:
Properly specify dns in network_metadata

The network-info spec states that dns should be specified as a service
in the network-info.json.

Change-Id: Ibdcc83f73e5ebca97d6beca35ab432b7ddd9a0f7

[{'created': '2015-12-07 23:16:09.000000000', 'message': 'Eliminate unnecessary sleeps during no-op update

For an update that involves e.g. stepping through the whole graph and
verifying that nothing needs to be updated, we spend a lot of time sleeping
unnecessarilty. Every task will exit without yielding (i.e.
it will be complete after calling TaskRunner.start()), yet the
DependencyTaskGroup yields after each set of tasks so the minimum sleep
time in seconds is the maximum path length in the graph minus one.

This change fixes that by removing nodes from the graph immediately if they
are done immediately after having been started. Since the _ready() call
returns an iterator, this allows any later tasks that were blocking only on
this one to start immediately. To ensure that any tasks that are only
blocking on this one _do_ appear later, iterate over the graph in
topologically sorted order.

The potential downside to this would be any time that actions complete
quickly (i.e. without yielding), but we still need to throttle them. An
obvious case might be a resource type with no check_create_complete()
function - creating a lot of these in a row could result in quota failures
on the target API. However, the Resource.action_handler_task() task always
yields at least once even if there is no check, so this patch should not
change its behaviour.

Change-Id: I734561814d2784e710d0b9ec3ef7834f44f579b2
Closes-Bug: #1523303
'}]
commit_message:
Eliminate unnecessary sleeps during no-op update

For an update that involves e.g. stepping through the whole graph and
verifying that nothing needs to be updated, we spend a lot of time sleeping
unnecessarilty. Every task will exit without yielding (i.e.
it will be complete after calling TaskRunner.start()), yet the
DependencyTaskGroup yields after each set of tasks so the minimum sleep
time in seconds is the maximum path length in the graph minus one.

This change fixes that by removing nodes from the graph immediately if they
are done immediately after having been started. Since the _ready() call
returns an iterator, this allows any later tasks that were blocking only on
this one to start immediately. To ensure that any tasks that are only
blocking on this one _do_ appear later, iterate over the graph in
topologically sorted order.

The potential downside to this would be any time that actions complete
quickly (i.e. without yielding), but we still need to throttle them. An
obvious case might be a resource type with no check_create_complete()
function - creating a lot of these in a row could result in quota failures
on the target API. However, the Resource.action_handler_task() task always
yields at least once even if there is no check, so this patch should not
change its behaviour.

Change-Id: I734561814d2784e710d0b9ec3ef7834f44f579b2
Closes-Bug: #1523303

commit_message:
Remove image make module

This module has not been used since 6.1 when
we suspended support Centos based clusters.
Anyway, target image building must be a part
of deployment process not ISO build process, so
target images should be built on the master node
in runtime.

Closes-Bug: #1523931
Change-Id: I86d4b2c886ea7da3254ce95033ce9f14d8a8e191

commit_message:
Remove the remaining mockups

At this point the pages which we originally mocked up have all been
implemented. They served as a useful reference when we were first
bootstrapping the project, but we've grown beyond them now. This
also removes the last remaining bits of the license quagmire we
had with using highcharts since it is no longer in the code base
at all.

Change-Id: Icc3173b959ec0417f5ecd3804cf10d7d41ebfbe4

commit_message:
Add test detail page

This adds a new page for a single test's details. It displays a
runtime graph and a stacked area graph of test statuses for the
specified individual test across all runs over the past 30 days.

Change-Id: Ib1f5aaaaf49315e2b00d38407e07702922f3d96f

commit_message:
Rework get_test_runs_for_test() rest api

This commit reworks the get_test_runs_for() rest api call and changes
it's basic behavior. The first thing done is the numeric data is split
from the non-numeric data in the response. This was done to enable
mean based resampling on the numeric data. This is necessary because
the other large change to the api is that a running mean and a running
std dev are added to the response. This was done to enable more
detailed graphs to the UI for the run_time of a single test.
To perform the running mean and std dev pandas is added to the
requirements for the rest api.

Change-Id: I3416dc0cad24c90405ac437df31c39b59f524d88

commit_message:
create path, `/var/lib/nova`, in nova-base

Without root privileges, nova process can't create and access the path,
`/var/lib/nova`.
Create the path and change the permission.

Change-Id: I6e5650298041b672bf386c50ccb68a6a80f9de43
Closes-Bug: #1523753

commit_message:
Run libvirtd as root

Currently we are not creating any non-root user for running
libvirt daemon. That should be done in the future, but currently
when we don't have such a user, libvirtd should be runned by
root.

Change-Id: Ieb0d8bd068b591f522548628b0bfffbe206b749e
Related-Bug: #1523630

commit_message:
Add murano external test-suite run as system test

- Add system test with murano external test-suite run for
ha one controller setup.
- Add system test with murano external test-suite run for
ha setup.

These tests is a part of a global qa initiative to move
all of the MOS integration tests to swarm execution.
These test suites will be launched nightly on a
dedicated server with extended resources like RAM and CPU.

Closes-Bug: #1522391
Change-Id: I8affe9e6a82478acd38db046d24b669d1f7be146

commit_message:
Use reno for release notes

The OpenStack Release team has created a great release notes management
tool that integrates with Sphinx. Start using it. For reference on how
to use it, see http://docs.openstack.org/developer/reno/

Change-Id: I57692d720174fedb68ab2f52d5a4c496a6d993b2

commit_message:
Remove empty tabs in freezer dashboard

remove empty tab for job edition
remove possibility to add job without interval if start and end date
are provided
show a message when a job is started/stoped

Resolves bug: 1523497

Change-Id: Iff39fc9e813969672eecd48d9084fd100bcf611c

commit_message:
Extend hiera task to improve plugin support

* Add hiera_config type to mange hiera.yaml
* Plugins can put their overrides to /etc/hiera/plugins/
* Running hiera_config again will gather override files
  and insert records for them to the main config file after
  the basic elements
* Or, it metadata_yaml_file is present, hiera_config can
  take the list of enabled plugins and add records for them
  instead of scanning the plugins directory

Closes-Bug: 1512456
DocImpact: add information about placing plugin data files to /etc/hiera/plugins/ instead of other files.
Change-Id: Ifdb27708a2457e8c1430695bb2412594806d211f

commit_message:
More useful message when using direct driver import

In the Liberty release, we switched to using entrypoints for
specifying the driver or auth plugin. The deprecation message
didn't mention the driver name that was specified, nor did it
mention where to look for the expected names, so it was not
user friendly.

Closes-Bug: 1513102
Change-Id: I02e265684b26686523da9d648b37675feb052978

for knowing the version instead of modifying the setup.cfg file.

Exclude DHCPv6 tests and Adv Ops

Revisit these tests and fix problems in later patches,
at this time exclude them from tempest

commit_message:
Add method for setting virtual disk IOPS limits

This method is required by the Nova Hyper-V driver in order to
support storage QoS specs.

Note that the minimum IOPS are not guaranteed, but events will be
emited when the IOPS level goes bellow this threshold.

Change-Id: Ic79215d90a8ea3231fcc3aad8e6f6a510eb7e3a3

commit_message:
Hyper-V: refactors utilsfactory

The Hyper-V API can change from a version to another (e.g. new
features), requiring a new Utils class to be added for specific
versions.

Refactors utilsfactory module. In this way, a new utils class
can be added without adding a new parameter when retrieving the
suitable class for windows version.

Change-Id: I3f58c911e6cf0206d6fbc9d62217f1534eaa1cbb
Partially-Implements: blueprint hyper-v-uefi-secureboot

commit_message:
Document Juno EOL

Juno is EOL in code repositories, mark the Juno guides as frozen
as well.

Since Juno is EOL-ed, there's no stable/juno branch anymore, we need to
use juno-eol instead of stable/juno.

Change-Id: I1115dc8009d31d56e62290ca4019c910993b0433

commit_message:
bagpipe: always pass network info to the agent

We currently need to send 'network_id', 'mac_address', 'ip_address',
'gateway_ip' to the agent, even in the absence of a BGPVPN bound
to the port. If we don't, this information will lack on an
update_bgpvpn RPC.

Change-Id: I9f6e59cc49cbe1aad7291898c867508c3b2d2b2d
Closes-Bug: 1523398

commit_message:
Refactor keypair existence check in Baymodel

A new magnum.api.attr_validator.py module is introduced to do the
validation towards OpenStack resources. Currently in Baymodel-creation,
the keypair validation code is duplicated. We should reduce the
duplicated code and unify the validation both in Bay and Baymodel.

Change-Id: Iba1bfad00c97f90d28501e65b73eed33be05e40f
Partial-Bug: #1522060

commit_message:
Move antlr version choice out of setup.py

Purpose:
Restore vanilla setup.py so it doesn't clash with automated updates

Change:
Moved antlr version choice logic to compile.py, the first place antlr is loaded
symlink manipulation based on __file__ rather than cwd for dependability

Change-Id: I790e871a40a624da1ca4c60c5f7e73c31e96a18b

commit_message:
Add tox.ini with pep8 tests to fix CI

* Add tox.ini with pep8 tests so 'gate-fuel-web-pep8' is able to
  actually run
* Ignore all existing pep8 errors and warnings to unblock merging in
  stable/6.1, but prevent any more pep8 errors and warnings

Change-Id: Iad59da7f8e5af901e7c9fa830f3a6ebe81d021b3
Related-Bug: #1511787

commit_message:
ec2-api job: limit tempest workers for testing

because ec2-api functional tests are very aggressive then
four workers can exceed quotas. but two workers should work well
as we saw in the past.

commit_message:
Switch aodh to use os_service_default fact

This change switches the aodh module to use the os_service_default
fact for configuration options that default to '<SERVICE DEFAULT>'.

Related-bug: #1515273
Change-Id: I05488c8bdcb5f54976a17aa25bf8a3b9d46627bb
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add retry decorator to methods adding/modifying resources

Adding virtual resources was consistently failing on our CIs,
especially when attaching the configdrive.

This patch attempts to fix this by adding the same decorator
that was used for the modify_virt_resource method, which had
avoided similar issues.

This is applied to the _modify_virtual_system method as well
for the same reason.

Change-Id: I1d3b0deb0682857b5cc688a25876868ecc26bcf0

commit_message:
Added execution of MOS tests to SWARM

We have a lot of integration tests for MOS verification
in upstream and in separate repository
https://github.com/Mirantis/mos-integration-tests.
We are going to move all our tests to one jenkins with
SWARM tests and this is why we need to add system tests
which will execute all integration tests in SWARM test suite.

These tests will be executed on the separate environment
as well as Tempest tests or integration tests for Sahara
and Murano deployments validation.

We need to add SWARM tests which will export all required
variables and will run run_tests.sh script from
https://github.com/Mirantis/mos-integration-tests.

Change-Id: I9ed6625a2a57a9aa6f2b65d9b3cf94894c70519b
Closes-Bug: #1523436

commit_message:
Add Code Contribution Guide for Ironic

Add a code contribution guide for Ironic. This should be useful for
developers to consider some key points when write and review
Ironic code.

First introduces things related to live-upgrade which consists
of RPC version and Object version.

Change-Id: I1d243a20151827a35aed465061befbcf65f96474
Implements: blueprint online-upgrade-support

commit_message:
Fix state_info details for with-items task error

For workflow with error in a with-items task, the workflow state_info should
only include the output for action executions that erred.

Change-Id: Iad1a1af1d68d7810d56bcb5335fe31f54593aba4
Closes-Bug: #1522647

commit_message:
Fix trusty based slave bootstrap

* Sync fix-configs-on-startup with fuel-main/bootstrap
* Due wrong permission for trusty/etc\usr folders, after
rsync's files into chroot system - ntp fails to run due Access Denied
error
* fix ubuntu cloud-init hook for ntp.drift
* nailgun-agent runs only from cron
* fix file permission for trusty bootstrap
* add 'psmisc' for fuel-agent requirements
  Centos7 don't install it by default, otherwise mcollective
  container - which used for IBP

Change-Id: Ifecbc4220df8ae77f7373d4b342aa1e72deb9059
Closes-Bug: #1522406

subject: Install python-pip package inside nailgun container Some tests build plugins inside nailgun container. For some reasons python-pip package is not installed in container by default. To make possible install Fuel Plugin Builder we should install pip.

commit_message:
Install python-pip package inside nailgun container
Some tests build plugins inside nailgun container.
For some reasons python-pip package is not installed in
container by default.
To make possible install Fuel Plugin Builder we should
install pip.

Change-Id: I170143ffda167d1146b77dbb531bdeb3f7f7f940
Closes-Bug: 1523874

commit_message:
Add OneOf smart type

It is a new smart type, that verifies function parameter
whether it belongs to the on of the specified in the function
declaration classes.

Targets blueprint mock-context-manager

Change-Id: I9eccdf3af1802c731bfdfb93df92c4ad902a4d34

commit_message:
Reset task state_info on task re-run

After re-running a task that was in ERROR state with state_info populated, the
state_info does not get reset after state is updated to RUNNING or SUCCESS.
The state_info retain the previous error details.

Change-Id: I2bc308224b1c4fca7c7fa5a40e6198aba1fe3e3b
Closes-Bug: #1522593

commit_message:
Allow ramdisk_id, kernel_id to be null on schema

Since is possible to create images with no
ramdisk_id, kernel_id parameters on glance v1,
then the schema-image.json needs to be modified to
allow null, string values for both attributes
and prevent LP #1447193 to happen with a glance v2
client.

Change-Id: I1319a1f6bdb69db90f9be7cf34df62cbd8538969
Closes-Bug: #1516330
Related-Bug: #1447193
(cherry picked from commit e39d2209a514c970127141a23864f86c630bddc3)

commit_message:
Update to pylint 1.4.5.

Pylint 1.4.5 is a dependency-only-change - it caps astroid, which
pylint uses to parse Python code. astroid 1.4.0 was backwards
incompatible. Switch to using 1.4.5, so that we can eventually unpin
astroid in preparation for projects moving to pylint 1.5 in future.

We cannot remove the astroid cap until all projects are using 1.4.5,
otherwise projects that are still dealing with the astroid mess will
be unable to sync a cap for it. Once all projects are on 1.4.5, we can
remove it trivially.

Change-Id: I1ff29325947723c7136272bc873cafa769619063

commit_message:
Remove wsgi reset_pool_size_to_default test

Test case reset_pool_size_to_default listen on default Ironic port.
So when it running on same host with ironic-api, test fails.

oslo.service contains such test case, so we can just remove it:
https://github.com/openstack/oslo.service/blob/master/oslo_service/tests/test_wsgi.py#L225

Closes-Bug: #1523809
Change-Id: I36faa5280dd0e4feb0a708a4d601cd870053f918

commit_message:
Move fuel-bootstrap-image-set to support centos7

* don't kill nonexistent supervisord, just restart service
* fix variable typo in  build_ubuntu_bootstrap func

Change-Id: Ic85f2f69119a708ffc23edbce9ad66ff72e6c000
Blueprint: master-on-centos7
Breaks: centos6 ubuntu-bootstrap switch

Remove `validate_ip_address` validator.

It is already merged on the puppetlabs-stdlib module:

https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-stdlib/commit/88a9a314c3e9cccbea5add95081655f2c14ec4c1

And we don't need to carry with this validation anymore.

Most of the services that use Keystone (and Keystone itself) changed
their default role to "_member_" about 2 years ago. DevStack still uses
"Member", which can cause unexpected issues. This patch changes any

commit_message:
Remove remnants of "Member" role

Most of the services that use Keystone (and Keystone itself) changed
their default role to "_member_" about 2 years ago. DevStack still uses
"Member", which can cause unexpected issues. This patch changes any
remaining incorrect settings.

Change-Id: I37088b5145d8b7300ce88caeed7f4e6c94ab05de
Closes-Bug: 1330132

commit_message:
Python3 readiness for congress/api

Notable changes:
- Encode/decode webob requests/results using utf-8
- Explicit sort key for comparison across types
- Check for length of trace in test_policy_model (consulted test author)
- Explicit conversion of dict view objects to lists
- Removed deprecated use of Exception.message

Result: all congress/tests/api/* tests pass under tox -epy34.

Partially implements blueprint: support-python3

Change-Id: If55dcaec937a481b92f367673effc0e63ee57c44

commit_message:
Python3 readiness for congress/datasources

Changes: Semantics-preserving changes for compatibility with Py27 & Py34

Result: all congress/tests/datasources/* tests pass under tox -epy34.

Partially implements blueprint: support-python3

Change-Id: I00bc2db90d7a756cfa857087ae479012bc6a522d

commit_message:
Fix event filtering in event-show

The event-show API was broken recently by not filtering with the given
event ID. This fixes the issue.

Change-Id: I0a37b27049986ad2ed8c19a18861f897c739e64d
Closes-Bug: #1523807

commit_message:
Remove juno handling from manila Jenkins jobs

With stable/juno eol'ed, we do not need to check anymore for
stable/juno, remove special handling.

Change-Id: I790fa8bd8eedca6d8007314f8ffa70232cbe22ba
